OSS is trending too commercial
text:
Shifting from RH/CentOS model to pseudo-free, walled-garden, and AGPL.

- Opscode->Progress Chef now requires an Oracle-like login.

- Canonical now requires Pro licensing for security updates.

- Grafana Apache 2.0 -> AGPL (radioactive).

- Minio Apache 2.0 -> AGPL (radioactive).

- MongoDB AGPL -> SSPL (even more radioactive).

Seems like CFEngine3, SugarCRM footgunning.
